Method Detail

getCommonAncestorState

IVersionableHandle getCommonAncestorState()
Returns the nearest identifiable common ancestor between the proposed current state and the old current state.

Note: The operation would haved failed if there was no common ancestor.

Returns:
the common ancestor state, or null if the common state was when the item was not present (for example, an add-add conflict)

getSelectedContributorState

IVersionableHandle getSelectedContributorState()
Returns the state which the workspace has selected as a contributor to this particular conflict.

Returns:
the state which is considered to be part of the conflict, where each element could be null to represent a deleted item.

the state which is considered to be part of the conflict, where each element could be null to represent a deleted item.

getProposedContributorState

IVersionableHandle getProposedContributorState()

the state which is considered to be part of the conflict, where each element could be null to represent a deleted item.

getMergeDetails

java.util.Collection getMergeDetails()
Get the merge details that are still outstanding. This data is opaque to SCM, it is defined by the Filesystem component.

Returns:
a collection of strings, never null
